# Open Earth Polar Model: References

## Foundational Theories and Inspirations

- Nicola Tesla – Wireless energy transmission, resonance theory
- Johannes Kepler – Celestial mechanics, elliptical orbits
- Albert Einstein – Spacetime curvature, General Relativity
- Riemannian geometry – Basis of curvature equations
- Faraday & Maxwell – Electromagnetic field dynamics
- Ancient cosmological models – Geocentric frameworks revisited

## Experimental Observations

- Foucault's Pendulum – Direct evidence of Earth’s rotation
- Polar vortex and asymmetry studies (NOAA)
- Gravity variation measurements by gravimeters (non-satellite)
- Cavendish Experiment – Local gravity measurement
- Muon deflection experiments at different altitudes
- Solar analemma and equinox measurements

## Related Open Projects

- Open Source Geophysics (OSGeo)
- Geospace Modeling and Observations (NSF-funded)
- OpenRelativity – MIT open simulation platform
- Flat Earth / Geocentric Critique Journals (non-mainstream)

## Suggestions for Independent Verification

- Long-term shadow tracking (sundial or gnomon method)
- Pendulum and gyroscope behavior over latitude
- Open data from Antarctic and Arctic science bases
- Citizen science magnetic anomaly recordings
- Sound wave behavior at various latitudes

---

We encourage further contributions and experiment proposals from independent researchers worldwide.
